## 10. Detailed Phase Plan

### Phase 1: Project Setup + Database (Day 1, Part 1)
1. Initialize Next.js 15 project with TypeScript
2. Install TailwindCSS v4, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion
3. Set up Supabase client libraries
4. Write and execute SQL migrations (schema, enums, indexes, RLS)
5. Create seed data script

### Phase 2: Authentication + UI Shell (Day 1, Part 2)
1. Supabase Auth тАФ email/password registration
2. Role selection (rider/driver) on signup
3. Middleware for role-based route protection
4. Basic layout: Navbar, route shells for all pages
5. Landing page (Hero + features + CTA)

### Phase 3: ML Pipeline (Day 2, Part 1)
1. Generate synthetic dataset (1000+ rides with geo, time, fare)
2. Feature engineering (Haversine distance, time encoding, normalization)
3. Train KMeans + DBSCAN тЖТ compare silhouette scores
4. Train Linear Regression + Random Forest тЖТ compare MAE/RMSE/R┬▓
5. Build driver ranking function
6. Save all models with joblib

### Phase 4: FastAPI ML Service (Day 2, Part 2)
1. Set up FastAPI project with model loading
2. `POST /cluster` тАФ cluster ride requests
3. `POST /predict-fare` тАФ predict solo/shared fare
4. `POST /rank-driver` тАФ return ranked driver list
5. Test endpoints with sample data

### Phase 5: Core Backend Logic (Day 3, Part 1)
1. Ride request creation (stores in Supabase, triggers ML)
2. Next.js API routes proxy to FastAPI
3. Driver fetching + acceptance flow
4. Ride status updates (requested тЖТ accepted тЖТ ongoing тЖТ completed)
5. Store ML results in DB

### Phase 6: Full Frontend (Day 3, Part 2 + Day 4)
1. Rider dashboard тАФ map, ride request form, active ride display
2. Driver dashboard тАФ incoming requests, accept/decline, toggle availability
3. Ride tracking page тАФ live map, status timeline, fare breakdown
4. Leaflet map integration with markers and routes

### Phase 7: Realtime + GPS (Day 4)
1. Supabase realtime subscriptions on `rides` table
2. Browser geolocation for driver position updates
3. Update `driver_locations` every 5 seconds
4. Live driver marker on rider's map

### Phase 8: Rating + Analytics + Polish (Day 5)
1. Post-ride rating flow
2. Driver average rating calculation (Supabase function)
3. Analytics dashboard тАФ cluster viz, fare charts, model metrics
4. Loading skeletons, error states, empty states
5. Framer Motion page transitions
6. Final testing

